[PATCH] adbd: reduce MAX_PAYLOAD for minimal build

Reduce MAX_PAYLOAD from 4096 to 1024 when ADBD_MINIMAL is defined
to significantly reduce per-packet memory allocation.

This is one of the most effective ways to reduce adbd's runtime
memory footprint. Each apacket structure contains a data buffer
of MAX_PAYLOAD bytes. With heavy ADB traffic, many packets may
be allocated simultaneously. Reducing this from 4KB to 1KB saves
3KB per packet.

For minimal USB shell-only use case, 1024 bytes is more than
sufficient since shell traffic typically consists of small
command/response chunks.

Signed-off-by: Buildroot User <user@example.com>
---
 core/adb/adb.h | 5 +++++
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+)

diff --git a/core/adb/adb.h b/core/adb/adb.h
index abcd123..efgh456 100644
--- a/core/adb/adb.h
+++ b/core/adb/adb.h
@@ -21,7 +21,12 @@
 
 #include "transport.h"  /* readx(), writex() */
 
+#ifdef ADBD_MINIMAL
+/* Reduce payload size to save memory in minimal mode */
+#define MAX_PAYLOAD 1024
+#else
 #define MAX_PAYLOAD 4096
+#endif
 
 #define A_SYNC 0x434e5953
 #define A_CNXN 0x4e584e43
